<span class="header1">CREATIVE PRODUCTION</span>
<p>The occupations in this field need people who are outgoing and creative.  Here are three examples.</p>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Managing Editor</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/BD/43333.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Managing Editor" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>A managing editor works in the publishing industry.  As a managing editor, you would oversee the hiring of writers and reporters.  You would also plan what is published.  You would know every aspect of putting together a newspaper or magazine.  Your job would be important.  But it would be stressful too.  Managing editors usually have other jobs in publishing before they are promoted to this job.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need a college degree in English, literature, or journalism for this job.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The yearly salary is $16,000 to $44,000.</blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Media Specialist</span><br /><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/BD/43278.jpg" width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Media Specialist" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>To see what a media specialist does, go to your school media center or library. A media specialist helps others get ready to give presentations or to chair meetings.  As a media specialist, you would suggest easy and effective ways to get a message across.  You would show people how to use the equipment.  You would also see that the equipment was in good repair.  You must be creative and be comfortable with technology to be good at this job.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need a Bachelor's Degree in educational media or in instructional technology for this job.  A part-time job at your local library would give you experience.  You might also volunteer in your school media center.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The yearly salary ranges from $20,000 to $45,000.</blockquote>

